# RPG — Project Configuration

## Project Overview
- **Unity Version:** 2022.3 LTS
- **Render Pipeline:** URP
- **Genre:** Action RPG (Diablo-like / top-down)
- **Target Platform:** PC (Steam) + Console (PS5 / Xbox)
- **Target FPS:** 60 baseline (min-spec PC and console performance mode); uncapped on high-refresh displays

## Architecture

### Assembly Structure
```
MyRPG.Core          — events, pooling, utilities, state machine, math
MyRPG.Stats         — stat system, modifiers, level/XP
MyRPG.Items         — inventory, equipment, crafting, loot
MyRPG.Combat        — damage, abilities, cooldowns, status effects
MyRPG.Quests        — quest definitions, objectives, tracking
MyRPG.Dialogue      — dialogue trees, NPC interaction
MyRPG.World         — scene management, spawners, interactables
MyRPG.UI            — HUD, menus, inventory UI, dialogue UI
MyRPG.Systems       — audio, save/load, settings, localization
MyRPG.Editor        — quest editor, stat balancer, loot table editor
```

### Key Systems
- **Stat System** — BaseStat + StatModifier (flat, percent add, percent multiply), ordering
- **Inventory** — slot-based, stackable items, equipment slots, weight/capacity
- **Combat** — real-time abilities, cooldowns, status effects (DoT, buff, debuff)
- **Quest System** — QuestDefinition SO, objectives (Kill/Collect/Talk/Location), rewards
- **Dialogue** — SO-based dialogue tree, choices, conditions, events
- **Save System** — ISaveable on all persistent objects, JSON save files, auto-save
- **Loot System** — weighted random tables, rarity tiers, procedural stats

### Scene Structure
- `S_Bootstrap` — persistent services (save, audio, input)
- `S_MainMenu` — title, character select, load game
- `S_Town` — hub area (shops, quest givers, crafting)
- `S_Dungeon_XX` — dungeon levels (procedurally generated or hand-crafted)
- `S_Boss_XX` — boss arenas

## Skills to Load
- `rpg` — stat system, quests, skill trees, combat
- `inventory-system` — items, equipment, crafting
- `dialogue-system` — NPC conversations
- `save-system` — full game state persistence
- `state-machine` — game states, enemy AI, ability states
- `procedural-generation` — dungeon generation, loot tables
- `character-controller` — top-down movement (WASD + mouse aim / gamepad twin-stick)
- `navmesh` — enemy pathfinding
- `ui-toolkit` — complex UI screens (ultrawide anchoring, gamepad focus navigation)
- `addressables` — asset loading, DLC and post-launch content

## Rules
Follow all rules in `.claude/rules/`. Platform guidance — PC/console performance budgets, BC7/BC5
texture compression, input and display handling — comes from `.claude/rules/pc-console.md`, which is
always in force; there is no platform skill to load.

## Key Conventions
- ALL game data is ScriptableObjects (items, abilities, enemies, quests, dialogue)
- Stats use modifier stacking: Flat → PercentAdd → PercentMultiply
- Equipment modifies stats by adding/removing StatModifiers
- Abilities are ScriptableObjects with cooldown, cost, effect list
- Status effects are timed stat modifiers + visual effects
- Save system serializes by ISaveable.SaveKey → JSON data
- Quests track progress via objective counters, fire events on complete

## Input Map
```
Player:
  Move — WASD / Left Stick
  Aim — Mouse position / Right Stick
  Attack — Left Mouse / Right Trigger
  Ability1-4 — 1-4 keys / Face buttons + shoulders
  Interact — E / A button (nearest interactable)
  Inventory — I / Y button
  QuestLog — J / D-pad Up
  Map — M / D-pad Down
  Dodge — Space / B button
```
Every binding is rebindable, and the HUD swaps prompts when the player switches between keyboard/mouse
and gamepad mid-session (see `.claude/rules/pc-console.md`).

## MCP Integration
Unity MCP at `http://localhost:8080/mcp`. Use for dungeon scene construction, NPC placement, UI screen building.
